Robin van Persie  scored three goals
as Arsenal beat Blackburn 7-1 to end a four-match winless run in
the English Premier League.  Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain scored twice and  Mikel Arteta  and
 Thierry Henry  added one goal each as Arsenal moved up two spots
to fifth place.  Van Persie â€™s hat trick pushes his league-leading
goal total to 22.  Morten Gamst Pedersen scored for Blackburn, which finished
with 10 men after Gael Givet received a red card just before
